'''Miyake-Hachimangū''' (三宅八幡宮) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]], in [[:en:Sakyo-ku|Sakyo-ku]], [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]], [[:en:Japan|Japan]]. The shrine is famous for worship to beneficial to children, such as [[:en:baby colic|baby colic]], academic achievement, safe delivery of childbirth. Because Mushi (虫, parasitic worms, insects, bugs) was thought to cause [[:en:baby colic|baby colic]] (疳の虫; kan-no mushi), the shrine also has worship for power to expel Mushi. Therefore the shrine is so-called Mushi-hachiman (虫八幡). Recently, many pieces of large size of [[:en:Ema (Shinto)|Ema]] was excavated, that represent worship to expel Mushi, and the Ema were designated as National Folk Cultural Properties.

== History ==
The shrine records say that [[:en:Ono no Imoko|Ono no Imoko]] built this shrine after his travel to the [[:en:Sui dynasty|Sui court]] in the era of [[:en:Empress Suiko|Empress Suiko]]. In the journey to China, he got sick in the Chikushi region, and prayed for the recovery of his health at Usa Hachimangū. He then successfully accomplished his mission as ''kenzuishi''. He built Miyake Hachimangū in his territory to thank Hachiman.

